$interpreted: Izumi: What a bummer. I was just getting into the swing of things.
Gretta: Phew... Another of your little pranks, No. 8?
Izumi: Ehh? Nothing to do with me, I swear it.
Gretta: *cough*... *cough* *cough*... What is it now...
Uzziah: ...So this is where it all comes to an end. Eighth Parhelion... and Fifth Parhelion.
Uzziah: The coming battle...
Izumi: What ends here, you irksome bum-beetle?
Uzziah: ...You're as stubborn as ever.
Izumi: I'll tell you something... It was we who always had to hunt down your ancestors. And now you're the one coming straight to us. I didn't realize you were in such a hurry to die.
Izumi: Didn't you learn your lesson back in the desert? Guardsman~
Gretta: He's the Guardsman?
Izumi: Yup. You'd know that if you didn't spend all your days frollicking up north, No. 5.
Gretta: He carries the core of Sdorica within him... No wonder he's powerful enough to summon monsters.
Izumi: Big deal~ Let's be honest, he's just a scapegoat for Vendacti.
Izumi: Hey, so, generations upon generations have been shouldering the heavy burden of that core. How many of you have died now, altogether~?
Uzziah: ...I'll die when my time comes, and I'll drag you to the grave with me. It's for me... to end the tragedy of the Guardsman's reincarnation!
Izumi: What should we do, No. 5? He really can't take a joke.
Gretta: This is all your fault, No. 8!
Uzziah: (Urgh... I can't let the bloodshed go on any longer... I'll have to annihilate them all, right here...)
Uzziah: (...This girl seems like she was really concerned about the sundial... Maybe I can open up a rift between them...)
Gretta: Ah!
Uzziah: (...Of course!)
Uzziah: Why... I thought you were...
Gretta: Family may fight, but they're still family... I'll take care of No. 8, no matter what.
Izumi: ...Eww, that's just... Well, anyway, that's how it is. We might not get along, but we can still call each other family~
Uzziah: Ugh...
Izumi: Looks like your luck's run out. Bye now.
Gretta: Butterflies..?
Izumi: Gah...!
Izumi: Heh, that actually kinda hurt... I was about to act like it was nothing...
Gretta: You don't need to act tough for my benefit!
Izumi: Well, worry about the sundial before you worry about me~
Izumi: ...It's really broken? Now what?
Gretta: How many time haves I told you, stop joking around!
Izumi: Oooh, are you mad?
Gretta: ...Fuming. But I forgive you. I know how sad you must have been to leave Atlas.
Izumi: ...You must be the only person on earth who can lecture me without stirring up my urge to murder them~
Izumi: You're a good person... It's a pity we chose our sides the way we did.
Gretta: Stop talking nonsense.
Gretta: Of course I'd always choose to be with my beloved family. Always did, always will. Forever.
Gretta: I'd be heartbroken if the northerners were ever to come to harm...
Gretta: But you, and the sect... are my family.
Izumi: ...I know.
Izumi: I'm sorry~
